{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionOrganizations have to take upon themselves the herculean task of going through hundreds, thousands, or millions of applicants' resumes in a bid to get the right talent rather efficiently.",
    "The bane of processing resumes rather than the scope of the applicants is that because of online job boards, social networks, and professional networking sites, the applicants are easily available, and scanning resumes manually is not only tedious but also costly.",
    "Hence, the process of attracting potential candidates and deploying further contesting measures has been sought to be automated by many recruiters to narrow down to the most promising candidates and ease the recruiting process.",
    "Traditional resume parsing is generally focused on keyword matching, which rarely captures the true depth of the candidate's skills to the job requirements.",
    "Such methods do not take into account the meaning of words, and, thus, are not very effective in finding suitable candidates who share the same profile."
  ]
}